This paper proposes a novel convolution layer for conditional generative adversarial networks (cGANs) to improve the generation of class conditional images. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks, specifically image generation, which suggests that the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the conditioning of the weights in the convolution layer, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of datasets such as CIFAR, LSUN, and ImageNet, which suggests that cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also possible sub-categories.
